Problem:
Let $g(x)$ be a function piecewise defined as \[g(x) = \left\{
\begin{array}{cl}
-x & x\le 0, \\
2x-41 & x>0.
\end{array}
\right.\] If $a$ is negative, find $a$ so that $g(g(g(10.5)))=g(g(g(a)))$.

Problem:
Let \[f(x) = \left\{
\begin{array}{cl}
-x + 3 & \text{if } x \le 0, \\
2x - 5 & \text{if } x > 0.
\end{array}
\right.\]How many solutions does the equation $f(f(x)) = 4$ have?
